ou’ll think this is the most beautiful update yet. Introducing a modern new design WordPress has gotten a facelift. 3.8 brings a fresh new look to the entire admin dashboard. […]</div></li></ul></div><div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.tv/2014/01/11/richard-martin-how-video-can-boost-your-traffic/\' title=\'    \'>WordPress.tv: Richard Martin: How Video Can Boost Your Traffic</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wordpress.tv/2014/01/11/becky-davis-you-can-make-a-living-with-wordpress/\' title=\'    \'>WordPress.tv: Becky Davis: You Can Make A Living With WordPress</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'http://wptavern.com/wpweekly-episode-133-does-your-plugin-suck?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=wpweekly-episode-133-does-your-plugin-suck\' title=\' All three contributing writers to WPTavern were able to be part of the first episode of WordPress Weekly for 2014. In this episode, we get you caught up on the headlines and give you our New Years resolutions. We had a great conversation about the launch of AppPresser and the Aesop story engine. Near the end of the show, Marcus Couch shared three new plugins from the repository that caught his eye.   Stories Discussed: Aesop Story Engine: An Open Source WordPress Plugin For Storytelling Mentor Others In The WordPress Community With WPMentor WordPress Core Trac Gets a Design Refresh, New Features and Enhancements AppPresser Launches First Mobile App Development Framework For WordPress Help Shape BuddyPress Development in 2014 Industry Night #5 – David Cramer, My Shortcodes and Caldera Engine Plugins Mentioned By Marcus Couch: Magic Liquidizer Responsive Table Read and Understood Plugin Organizer WPWeekly Meta: Next Episode: Friday, January 17th 3 P.M. Eastern – Special Guest David Bisset Subscribe To WPWeekly Via Itunes: Click here to subscribe Subscribe To WPWeekly Via RSS: Click here to subscribe Subscribe To WPWeekly Via Stitcher Radio: Cli